%% Data Flow Diagram - Data Science Pipelines Operator
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant API as DSP API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP MySQL
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>9000/443/TCP
    participant ArgoWF as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant TaskPod as Pipeline Task Pod
    participant MLMD as MLMD gRPC Server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant PAgent as Persistence Agent

    Note over User,PAgent: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission and Execution

    User->>Router: POST /apis/v1beta1/pipelines<br/>HTTPS, OpenShift auth
    Router->>RBAC: TLS reencrypt<br/>8443/TCP
    RBAC->>RBAC: SubjectAccessReview<br/>against K8s API
    RBAC->>API: Forward request<br/>8888/TCP, TLS (service-ca)
    API->>DB: Store pipeline metadata<br/>3306/TCP, TLS, password auth
    API->>S3: Store pipeline spec<br/>S3 credentials
    API->>ArgoWF: Create Workflow CR<br/>via K8s API
    ArgoWF->>TaskPod: Create task pods<br/>via K8s API

    Note over User,PAgent: Flow 2: Artifact and Metadata Tracking

    TaskPod->>MLMD: Log execution metadata<br/>8080/TCP gRPC, TLS
    MLMD->>DB: Store lineage data<br/>3306/TCP, TLS, password
    TaskPod->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>S3 credentials
    PAgent->>API: Sync run status<br/>8888/TCP, TLS

    Note over User,PAgent: Flow 3: Operator Health Checks

    Note right of API: DSPO Controller periodically<br/>checks MariaDB and S3 health<br/>before marking DSPA as Ready
